    "For a detailed explanation on how the marginal and conditional distributions are calculated in BDA and W-BDA, the reader is referred to Wang et al. (2017).",
    "Figure 15 presents the BDA and W-BDA results when using μ ¼ 0:5 for Scenario 1 from Table 7.",
    "The left figure shows the M-JDA mapping, the middle is the BDA mapping, and on the right is the W-BDA mapping.",
    "To reiterate, in scenario one, the source domain contains data from all classes, whereas the target domain has classes two and three.",
